### Stomping the Timestamps

Both timestamps were manipulated using PowerShell, a method readily available to any attacker on a Windows system.

#### Stomp the Last Write (Modified) Time

```powershell
powershell -command "(Get-Item 'C:\Users\jderr\OneDrive\Documents\Timestomped file.txt').LastWriteTime = '05/20/2022 10:30 AM'"
```

#### Stomp the Creation Time

```powershell
powershell -command "(Get-Item 'C:\Users\jderr\OneDrive\Documents\Timestomped file.txt').CreationTime = '05/20/2021 11:30 AM'"
```

The file's timestamps now appear to predate the incident by several years, making it indistinguishable from pre-existing system files during a standard timeline review.

