## Finding 5.2 – Zeroed Subseconds on Created (0x10)

Legitimate NTFS timestamps include nanosecond precision.

Many timestomping tools cannot reproduce this level of precision, resulting in timestamps ending with:

```
.0000000
```

A **Created (0x10)** timestamp ending in `.0000000` is a strong secondary indicator of timestamp manipulation.

This indicator should always be considered alongside other evidence because some legitimate archive or copy operations can also produce zeroed subseconds.

