## Finding 5.3 – Value Present in Created (0x30)

In MFTECmd's CSV output, the **Created (0x30)** column is only populated when the timestamp stored within `$FILE_NAME` differs from the timestamp stored in `$STANDARD_INFORMATION`.

The presence of a value in this column confirms that the two timestamp records differ, making it another important indicator of timestamp manipulation.

> **Note:** The **SI < FN** and **uSec Zeroes** columns are generated by MFTECmd during parsing and are not stored directly within the raw `$MFT`.

